cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC

The paper deals with the complementation of B\"uchi automata, which is a topic in formal language theory and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the complexity of the complementation algorithm, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of B\"uchi complementation in formal verification, which could place it under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
